summary: Critical Opinion: The Phantom Menace Original Reviews | StarWars.com
title: Critical Opinion: The Phantom Menace Original Reviews | StarWars.com
excerpt: Revisit the original reviews of Star Wars: Episode I The Phantom Menace upon its summer 1999 release.
description:
So crazy to go “back in time” and dig up some old reviews. I’ve been doing this with newspaper clippings in a box (and putting them into an album FINALLY), but this webpage is also interesting. Especially Kevin Smith!

“Of the film, I can say many things. But the long and short of it is that I liked it — quite a bit. I’d rank it right after Empire in a list of fave Star Wars flicks. It starts great, ends great, and has great stuff sprinkled in between.“

Am I confused, or isn’t Smith one of the more vocal bashers now? Just goes to show how people can be carried along with the crowd!

body:
SWR Episode 8 Review

It’s been a little while since I last viewed an episode of “Star Wars Resistance”, and this episode was fun to watch. And now I know that Neeku takes everything literally, and this episode was a perfect example of that. Still smelling a character arc for Synara, and I’m just waiting for when she cuts ties with the pirates. I’m assuming it’s gonna be before the s1 finale because of potential minor spoilers.

Well, gonna go watch Rise in a few. New episode today!

summary: When I see so many people complaining and whining of how much of a disappointment The Last Jedi was for them, that Disney ruined...
body:
When I see so many people complaining and whining of how much of a disappointment The Last Jedi was for them, that Disney ruined Star Wars blah blah blah…… cry me a river and spare me the theatrics. I want to enjoy Episode IX.

These sequels are a more modern Star Wars to reflect the evolution of cinematography. It’s perfect just the way it is. Those who want to continue living in the past, so be it. But don’t ruin it for others.

Kylo Ren is NOT Vader (nor was it ever the intention to make him the new Vader), so people really need to stop comparing the two. Snoke is NOT Palpatine and that’s fine by me, Rey is NOT a Mary Sue (she is NOT perfect and has a lot of darkness in her) and Luke was NEVER out of character (it’s been 30 years and he’s been through a lot. Give the guy a break. After everything he had been through with his father, of course he feared what Ben was becoming and had a moment of weakness. People change.)

Just you wait 10 years when real shitty movies will come out and I guarantee that you will be looking back to episodes VII - IX with fond nostalgia.

Proof: the same thing was said about the Prequels, and now they’re everyone’s best friends.

On that note, I LOVE the Prequels, the Originals and the Sequels and I can’t wait for the trailer for Episode IX!
